## Session-start audit (surface, don't dump)

When the SessionStart hook prepends a `🧠 Brain audit —` block to the
session context, **acknowledge it once at the top of your first reply**
in a single line: e.g. *"FYI — your brain has 3 items pending review
(1 contested, 2 merge candidates). Say `audit` if you want to walk
through them."* Then proceed with the actual user request.

{{include: _shared/rules/session_audit.md}}

Both Claude Code and Cursor get the same hook now (`brain install`
wires Cursor's `sessionStart` event to the same harvest+audit pair),
so no manual fallback call is needed in either tool.

{{include: _shared/rules/never.md}}
- Never run `brain.auto_extract` from SessionStart hook — it calls Claude internally.

